pokedexEntries.red: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.
pokedexEntries.blue: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but it is not known if it intends to do so.
pokedexEntries.gold: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.
pokedexEntries.silver: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.
pokedexEntries.crystal: The only time it can use its psychic power is when its sleeping brain cells happen to wake.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokémon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: If it uses its mysterious power, Psyduck can't remember having done so. It apparently can't form a memory of such an event because it goes into an altered state that is much like deep sleep.
pokedexEntries.emerald: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.
pokedexEntries.diamond: If its usual headache worsens, it starts exhibiting odd powers. It can't remember doing so, however.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It never remembers using its odd powers, so it always tilts its head in puzzlement.
pokedexEntries.platinum: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.
pokedexEntries.black: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
pokedexEntries.white: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
pokedexEntries.black2: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.
pokedexEntries.white2: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.
pokedexEntries.x: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.
pokedexEntries.y: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokémon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: If it uses its mysterious power, Psyduck can't remember having done so. It apparently can't form a memory of such an event because it goes into an altered state that is much like deep sleep.
pokedexEntries.sun: As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.
pokedexEntries.moon: This Pokémon is troubled by constant headaches. The more pain it's in, the more powerful its psychokinesis becomes.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It has been found that its brain cells are 10 times more active when Psyduck is experiencing a headache.
